## BRANDING & DESIGN TOKENS

### Colours
```css
/* Use these exact CSS variable names throughout */
--color-primary:     #E07B20;   /* JC Brick orange — buttons, accents, section headers */
--color-primary-dark:#B85F10;   /* Hover state for orange elements */
--color-secondary:   #6B6B6B;   /* Grey — secondary text, dividers */
--color-dark:        #1A1A1A;   /* Near-black — headings, body text */
--color-light:       #F5F5F5;   /* Off-white — alternating section backgrounds */
--color-white:       #FFFFFF;
--color-accent:      #000000;   /* Black — trust bar, footer */
```

In Tailwind config, extend with:
```js
colors: {
  brand: {
    orange:      '#E07B20',
    'orange-dark':'#B85F10',
    grey:        '#6B6B6B',
    dark:        '#1A1A1A',
    light:       '#F5F5F5',
  }
}
```

### Typography
- **Display / Headings**: `Barlow Condensed` (Bold 700, SemiBold 600) — strong, trade-appropriate, masculine without being aggressive. Pairs well with the orange brand colour.
- **Body**: `DM Sans` (Regular 400, Medium 500) — clean, highly legible on mobile, friendly without being soft.
- Load both via `next/font/google`. Never use Inter, Roboto, or Arial.
- H1: `text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight` (Barlow Condensed)
- H2: `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold` (Barlow Condensed)
- H3: `text-xl font-semibold` (Barlow Condensed)
- Body: `text-base leading-relaxed` (DM Sans)
- Trust/micro copy: `text-sm font-medium` (DM Sans)

### Spacing
- Section vertical padding: `py-16 md:py-24`
- Container max width: `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
- Card internal padding: `p-6 md:p-8`

### Design Aesthetic
- Dark hero sections (dark background, white text, orange CTA) alternating with light sections (off-white background)
- Orange used sparingly — CTAs, active states, section accents, stat highlights
- No gradients on the orange — solid fills only
- Subtle texture on dark sections: a faint noise/grain overlay at 3–5% opacity gives depth without looking designed
- Brick-pattern SVG motif (subtle, low-opacity) permitted as background texture on the hero only — must not distract from the headline
- Photography-first design — hero and service sections should be built to showcase Jamie's work photos prominently
- Mobile-first always — design for 390px width first, scale up

