## SCHEMA — JSON-LD IMPLEMENTATION

All schema is injected as `<script type="application/ld+json">` tags in the `<head>` via Next.js metadata or a `JsonLd` component. Never inline schema in the body. All schema values are pre-built in the Developer Brief — copy exactly, do not recalculate.

### Schema types required per page:

| Page | Schema Types |
|---|---|
| All pages (root layout) | `LocalBusiness`, `Organization` |
| Home | `AggregateRating`, `Review` (×3) |
| All service pages | `FAQPage` |
| FAQ page | `FAQPage` |
| All pages except Home | `BreadcrumbList` |

### JsonLd Component Pattern
```tsx
// /components/JsonLd.tsx
export function JsonLd({ data }: { data: object }) {
  return (
    <script
      type="application/ld+json"
      dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(data) }}
    />
  )
}
```
Use in `<head>` via layout or page metadata slot — never in `<body>`.

