## ACCESSIBILITY — WCAG 2.1 AA

- Every form field: visible `<label>` above the input — placeholder text is not a substitute
- All interactive elements keyboard-accessible — visible focus ring on tab
- Tab order follows logical visual order
- All modals, accordions (FAQ), dropdowns: keyboard accessible, ARIA roles applied
- Colour contrast: white text on `#E07B20` orange passes AA — verify with contrast checker
- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons (e.g. mobile menu toggle)
- Skip-to-content link as first element in `<body>`:
```tsx
<a href="#main-content" className="sr-only focus:not-sr-only">
  Skip to main content
</a>
```

---

## PERFORMANCE — CORE WEB VITALS TARGETS

| Metric | Target | Key Rules |
|---|---|---|
| LCP | < 2.5s | Hero image must use `priority={true}`. Preload hero image in `<head>`. |
| CLS | < 0.1 | All images must have explicit `width` and `height`. Fonts loaded via `next/font`. |
| INP | < 200ms | Minimise client components. No unnecessary JS on load. |

- Run PageSpeed Insights on mobile before and after launch. Document the score.
- All images: WebP format, compressed before placement in `/public/images/`
- No Google Tag Manager or third-party scripts loaded synchronously
- Any analytics script: load with `strategy="afterInteractive"` via `next/script`

